@startuml
' @id(DOM-ARCH-SPEC)
' @desc(DOM-ARCH-SPEC, "The structured, machine-readable architectural source of truth under .mdd/architecture/: components.yml (logical/deployable components — kind, ownership of domain @ids, dependencies, tech), decisions.yml (architecture decisions as data — status, context, decision, consequences, supersedes chain; append-only so the list is the decision history), and constraints.yml (cross-cutting architectural rules with rationale + applies_to). The authoritative what+why beside the diagrams; scaffolded SeededOnce by mdd init, authored by /mdd-kickoff, diffed via git today (a structured mdd arch verb is a planned follow-up).")
' Objective-side domain for the architectural source of truth (cycle 0028).
title Architecture source of truth (objective)

class ArchitectureSpec {
  + dir : Path
}
class Component {
  + id : String
  + name : String
  + kind : ComponentKind
  + owns : List<Id>
  + dependsOn : List<Id>
  + tech : String
}
enum ComponentKind {
  service
  library
  datastore
  adapter
  ui
  external
}
class Decision {
  + id : String
  + title : String
  + status : DecisionStatus
  + date : Date
  + context : String
  + decision : String
  + consequences : String
  + supersedes : String?
  + supersededBy : String?
}
enum DecisionStatus {
  proposed
  accepted
  superseded
  deprecated
}
class Constraint {
  + id : String
  + rule : String
  + appliesTo : List<Id>
  + rationale : String
}

ArchitectureSpec "1" o-- "*" Component : components.yml >
ArchitectureSpec "1" o-- "*" Decision : decisions.yml >
ArchitectureSpec "1" o-- "*" Constraint : constraints.yml >
Component --> ComponentKind
Decision --> DecisionStatus

note bottom of Decision
  Append-only: a change supersedes a prior decision
  (supersedes / supersededBy) rather than rewriting
  it, so decisions.yml IS the decision history
  (OCL-ARCH-DECISION-HAS-STATUS,
  OCL-ARCH-SUPERSEDE-LINKED).
end note
note bottom of Component
  owns / dependsOn reference diagram @ids (DOM-/CMP-);
  components.yml stays in sync with the component
  diagrams (OCL-ARCH-COMPONENTS-IN-SYNC).
end note
@enduml
